# COBOL Copy Element Naming Conventions

## Program Name Structure: `PPTNNNNN.CBL`

| Position | Meaning | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| **PP** (2 chars) | Subsystem prefix | GM, OK, OS, RS, RK, IL, DB, VDH, AA, BR, D3/D4/D5, TM, VS, SF, XX, GX |
| **T** (1 char) | Program type | H, V, B, F, X, A |
| **NNNNN** | Functional name | KORN, OPER, FATR, DELI |

### Program Type Codes (3rd character)

| Code | Type | Norwegian | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| **H** | Main screen | Hovedbilde | Interactive screen program |
| **V** | Validation | Validering | Validation for an H-program |
| **B** | Batch | Batch | Background/batch program |
| **F** | Function | Funksjon | Shared function/subroutine |
| **X** | Extract | Eksport | Data extraction |
| **A** | API | API/DLL | API/DLL interface |

