## Copy Element Extensions and Roles

| Extension | Full Name | Folder | Role |
|---|---|---|---|
| **.CPB** | Copy Program Block | `cpy/` | Screen data blocks (LINKAGE SECTION), name matches H-program |
| **.CPY** | Copy | `cpy/` | General working-storage copybooks |
| **.DCL** | Declare | `sys/cpy/` | DB2 host variable declarations (2-4 char table abbreviation) |
| **.CPX** | Copy Extended | `sys/cpy/` | Extended copybooks (RS/OA subsystems) |
| **.MF** | Micro Focus | runtime | Micro Focus system copybooks (e.g. `DS-CNTRL.MF`) |
| **.GS** | Generated Screen | `gs/` | Binary screen layout file |
| **.IMP** | Import | `imp/` | Dialog System import files, mirrors CPB names |

## COPY Statement Syntax Variants

```cobol
COPY "DEFCPY.CPY".        -- Quoted with extension (most common)
COPY 'KUN.DCL'.           -- Single-quoted with extension
COPY SQLENV.              -- Bare name, no quotes (DB2 precompiler convention)
EXEC SQL INCLUDE SQLCA END-EXEC.  -- Only used for SQLCA
```

- Both single and double quotes are used interchangeably
- `COPY ... REPLACING` is NOT used anywhere in this codebase
- `$SET DB2(COPY)` directive tells the precompiler to process COPY inside SQL DECLARE sections

## Program-to-Copybook Relationships

### Rule 1: H-programs always have a self-named .CPB
`RSHKORN.CBL` -> `COPY "RSHKORN.CPB"` (screen data block in LINKAGE SECTION)

### Rule 2: V-programs reference their H-program's .CPB
`GMVVDIK.CBL` -> `COPY 'GMHVDIK.CPB'` (validates data from the H-screen)

### Rule 3: Some programs have a matching .CPY
`RSHKORN.CBL` -> `COPY "RSHKORN.CPY"` (working-storage fields)

### Rule 4: DCL files use short DB2 table abbreviations
`KUN.DCL` = Kunder, `SOH.DCL` = Ordrehoder, `SOL.DCL` = Ordrelinjer, `VAR.DCL` = Vareregister

### Rule 5: EXEC SQL INCLUDE is only for SQLCA
All other DB2 copies use `COPY 'xxx.DCL'` inside `EXEC SQL DECLARE SECTION`

## Framework Copybooks (shared across all subsystems)

| Copybook | Purpose |
|---|---|
| DEFCPY.CPY | SQL error handling block (nearly universal) |
| REQFELL.CPY | Request/authorization framework |
| DSRUNNER.CPY | Dialog System runner interface |
| DSSYSINF.CPY | Dialog System info block |
| DS-CNTRL.MF | Dialog System control block |
| CURT.CPY | Date/time utilities |
| GMAUTILS.CPY | General utility functions |
| FLEX.CPY | Flexible parameter passing |
| LBLP.CPY | Label printing interface |
| GMASEMA.CPY | Semaphore/locking (batch) |

## File Exclusion Patterns (from AzureDevOpsGitCheckIn)

Files with these patterns are excluded as old/backup copies:
- Suffixes: `-OLD`, `_OLD`, `-GML`, `_GML`, `-GAMMEL`, `_GAMMEL`
- Names containing 8 consecutive digits (date stamps)
- Names containing spaces

## Folder Layout (VCPATH)

```
$VCPATH\src\cbl\          -- .CBL source files
$VCPATH\src\cbl\cpy\      -- .CPY and .CPB copybooks
$VCPATH\src\cbl\cpy\sys\cpy\  -- .DCL and .CPX system copybooks
$VCPATH\src\cbl\imp\      -- .IMP import files
$VCPATH\src\rex\           -- .REX REXX scripts
$VCPATH\src\bat\           -- .BAT/.CMD batch files
```

## Copybook Search Order (for COPY resolution)

1. Same folder as the CBL file
2. `cpy/` folder (`.CPY`, `.CPB`)
3. `sys/cpy/` folder (`.DCL`, `.CPX`)
4. COBCPY environment variable paths
